scene.message:
Kaneda: What do you want with{nl}
my place?{waitkey}Don't tell me you're debt{nl}
collectors!?{wait_fr:32} As you can see,{nl}
I haven't got any money!{waitkey}{clearbox}The ruins I was counting on{nl}
had no treasure at all.{nl}
My business is ruined!{waitkey}{ret}

{color:3}Katsue Kaneda{nl}
Was supposed to have suddenly{nl}
grown rich and to live in a{nl}
fine house, but...{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Honestly, Nanjo! Ms.{nl}
Kaneda's job is robbing ruins,{nl}
isn't it!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Tomb robbing — that's{nl}
hardly what you'd call a job.{waitkey}{clearbox}Besides, there's no way you{nl}
could do such a thing in{nl}
Japan today, is there?{waitkey}{clearbox}Honestly, Maki, the strange{nl}
things you say.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Tomb robbing? You can't{nl}
do that in Japan. Maki, what{nl}
a weird thing to say.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: Tomb robbing...?{wait_fr:32}{nl}
There's no way you could do{nl}
that.{waitkey}{clearbox}You're not a child. Don't{nl}
talk nonsense.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Come to think of it,{nl}
there was a rumor the old{nl}
lady got rich by ransacking{nl}
ruins.{waitkey}Going around about a year{nl}
ago, that.{waitkey}{clearbox}Sonomura, did you take that{nl}
at face value?{wait_fr:48} ...Oh right,{nl}
you're a different Sonomura.{waitkey}{ret}

Kaneda: Quit your yammering!{nl}
Now, if you've no business,{nl}
off with you!{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: {ctl0f:1}, Sonomura said{nl}
the Kaneda hag makes her{nl}
living by robbing ruins.{waitkey}{clearbox}In our town, that was nothing{nl}
more than a rumor.{waitkey}{clearbox}But in this town, it seems to{nl}
have become reality.{waitkey}{clearbox}Why has the rumor become{nl}
real?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: A rumor becoming{nl}
real...?{wait_fr:32} ...N-{wait_fr:21}no, my head{nl}
hurts... Hey everyone, let's{nl}
just go!{waitkey}{ret}

Kaneda: What's become of this{nl}
town!{waitkey}{clearbox}All of a sudden, everywhere's{nl}
gone to ruin!{waitkey}{clearbox}You lot are strong, aren't{nl}
you? Seeing this state of{nl}
things, don't you want to do{nl}
something about it?!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: ...{wait_fr:32}Sorry, granny.{nl}
We're running around trying{nl}
to do something about it too.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Mark, calm down... Maki{nl}
will surely be fine. Come,{nl}
let's hurry and search!{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: There, there, Mark.{nl}
Don't get so worked up!{waitkey}{clearbox}I'll have everything back to{nl}
normal in no time!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Don't get mad, Inaba...{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Everything'll be back to{nl}
normal real soon!{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: Calm down, Inaba. Just{nl}
a little more patience.{waitkey}{clearbox}Then I'll set everything back{nl}
to rights, you'll see.{waitkey}{ret}
